<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Group Flow Report</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: "Segoe UI", Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; color: #222; margin: 2cm; }
  h1   { color: #0072B2; border-bottom: 2px solid #0072B2; padding-bottom: 6px; }
  h2   { color: #0072B2; margin-top: 1.5em; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin-bottom: 1em; }
  th    { background: #0072B2; color: #fff; padding: 6px 10px; text-align: left; }
  td    { padding: 5px 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; }
  tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #f5f8fb; }
  .caveat { background: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #E69F00; padding: 8px 12px;
            margin: 0.5em 0; font-size: 12px; }
  .footer { margin-top: 2em; font-size: 11px; color: #aaa; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; padding-top: 6px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Group Flow Metrics — Summary Report</h1>

<p class="caveat">
  <strong>Note:</strong> Cross-squad comparison is intended as a diagnostic, not a
  performance ranking. Squads tackle different types of work and face different
  constraints. Use this view to identify patterns worth investigating together.
</p>

<h2>Squad Summary</h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Squad</th>
    <th>Median CT (d)</th>
    <th>85th CT (d)</th>
    <th>Avg throughput (/wk)</th>
    <th>Candidate constraint</th>
  </tr>
  {% for s in squad_summaries %}
  <tr>
    <td><strong>{{ s.name }}</strong></td>
    <td>{{ s.ct_p50 }}</td>
    <td>{{ s.ct_p85 }}</td>
    <td>{{ s.tp_mean }}</td>
    <td>{{ s.constraint }}</td>
  </tr>
  {% endfor %}
</table>

<div class="footer">
  Generated by Squad Flow Metrics · CT = cycle time (calendar days).
</div>

</body>
</html>
